        <h2 id="intro">Introduction</h2>

        <p>
            Brewing methods refer to the techniques used to extract flavor from coffee or tea.
            Different brewing methods can produce different results.
            Some methods are simple and quick, while others require patience and precision.
        </p>

        <h2 id="brewing-important">Why is Brewing Method Important?</h2>
        <p>
            The brewing method is essential because it can affect the taste and aroma of your coffee or tea.
            Different methods can highlight specific flavors or make the drink more or less bitter.
            Understanding and experimenting with various brewing methods can help you find the perfect cup of coffee or tea for your taste buds.
        </p>

        <h2 id="drip">Drip Coffee</h2>

        <img src="/static/images/drip.png" class="w-50 img-thumbnail rounded-3 border-1"/>

        <p>
            Drip coffee is a popular brewing method that involves putting ground coffee beans into a filter, which is placed in a coffee maker.
            Hot water is then poured over the beans, and the resulting coffee drips into a pot or carafe.
            Drip coffee is quick, easy, and produces a mild to medium-bodied flavor.
        </p>

        <h3>How To Make a Drip Coffee?</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Grind your coffee beans to a medium-coarse grind.</li>
            <li>Add the ground coffee to a paper filter inside the coffee maker.</li>
            <li>Pour hot water over the coffee and let it drip into the pot or carafe.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your coffee!</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Tips for Making the Perfect Drip Coffee</h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Use high-quality, fresh beans.</li>
            <li>Use filtered water.</li>
            <li>Clean your coffee maker regularly.</li>
            <li>Experiment with the amount of coffee and water to find your perfect ratio.</li>
            <li>Keep your coffee maker clean.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="french">French Press</h2>
        <img src="/static/images/frenchpress.png" class="w-50 img-thumbnail rounded-3 border-1"/>
        <p>
            The French press, also known as a press pot, is a brewing method that involves steeping ground coffee beans in hot water.
            The coffee is then separated from the grounds by pressing a plunger down through the water.
            The French press produces a full-bodied, richly flavored coffee.
        </p>

        <h3>How to Make French Press Coffee?</h3>

        <ol>
            <li>Grind your coffee beans to a coarse grind.</li>
            <li>Add the ground coffee to the French press.</li>
            <li>Pour hot water over the coffee.</li>
            <li>Let the coffee steep for about four minutes.</li>
            <li>Press the plunger down to separate the coffee from the grounds.</li>
            <li>Pour and enjoy your coffee.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Tips for Making the Perfect French Press Coffee</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use high-quality, fresh beans.</li>
            <li>Use filtered water.</li>
            <li>Experiment with the amount of coffee and water to find your perfect ratio.</li>
            <li>Keep your French press clean.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="pour">Pour-over</h2>
        <img src="/static/images/pourover.png" class="w-50 img-thumbnail rounded-3 border-1"/>
        <p>
            Pour-over is a brewing method that involves pouring hot water over ground coffee beans, which are held in a filter.
            The water is poured in a circular motion, allowing the coffee to bloom and extract evenly.
            Pour-over produces a clean, crisp, and flavorful cup of coffee.
        </p>

        <h3>How to Make Pour-over Coffee?</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Grind your coffee beans to a medium-fine grind.</li>
            <li>Add the ground coffee to a paper filter inside the pour-over dripper.</li>
            <li>Wet the coffee with hot water and let it bloom for about 30 seconds.</li>
            <li>Pour hot water over the coffee in a circular motion.</li>
            <li>Let the coffee drip into your cup.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your coffee!</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Tips for Making the Perfect Pour-over Coffee</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use high-quality, fresh beans.</li>
            <li>Use filtered water.</li>
            <li>Experiment with the amount of coffee and water to find your perfect ratio.</li>
            <li>Keep your pour-over dripper clean.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="espr">Espresso</h2>
        <img src="/static/images/espresso.png" class="w-50 img-thumbnail rounded-3 border-1"/>
        <p>
            Espresso is a brewing method that involves forcing pressurized water through finely ground coffee beans.
            This results in a highly concentrated and strong coffee with a creamy layer on top, called crema.
            Espresso is the base for many popular coffee drinks, such as lattes and cappuccinos.
        </p>

        <h3>How to Make Espresso?</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Grind your coffee beans to a fine grind.</li>
            <li>Pack the ground coffee into an espresso machine's portafilter.</li>
            <li>Turn on the machine to force hot water through the coffee.</li>
            <li>The result should be a concentrated shot of espresso.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Tips for Making the Perfect Espresso</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use high-quality, fresh beans.</li>
            <li>Use filtered water.</li>
            <li>Experiment with the grind size and amount of coffee to achieve the perfect flavor.</li>
            <li>Keep your espresso machine clean.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="cold">Cold Brew</h2>
        <img src="/static/images/coldbrew.png" class="w-50 img-thumbnail rounded-3 border-1"/>
        <p>
            Cold brew is a brewing method that involves steeping coarse ground coffee beans in cold water for several hours.
            The resulting coffee is less acidic and less bitter than traditional coffee.
            Cold brew is perfect for hot summer days and can be served over ice.
        </p>

        <h3>How to Make Cold Brew?</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Coarsely grind your coffee beans.</li>
            <li>Add the ground coffee to a large container or jar.</li>
            <li>Pour cold water over the coffee.</li>
            <li>Let the coffee steep in the fridge for 12-24 hours.</li>
            <li>Strain the coffee to remove the grounds.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your cold brew over ice.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Tips for Making the Perfect Cold Brew</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use high-quality, fresh beans.</li>
            <li>Use filtered water.</li>
            <li>Experiment with the amount of coffee and water to find your perfect ratio.</li>
            <li>Keep your container or jar clean.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
            There are many different brewing methods, each with its unique set of strengths and weaknesses.
            Whether you prefer a quick and easy cup of drip coffee or a full-bodied French press, there is a brewing method out there for everyone.
            Experiment with different methods and find the one that suits your taste buds.
        </p>
